主要翻译
 
burning adj (on fire)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 燃烧的 rán shāo de TC Traditional Chinese 燃燒的  
 -- Fire fighters raced to the burning building.
 -- 消防员赶到了燃烧的大楼现场。
 
burning adj figurative (desire: ardent)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 欲火中烧的 yù huǒ zhōng shāo de  
 -- He could barely control his burning desire.
 -- 他欲火中烧，几乎难以抑制。
 
burning adj figurative (sensation: stinging)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 灼烧的 TC Traditional Chinese 灼燒的  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 灼痛的 zhuó tòng de 
 -- The solution may cause a burning sensation.
 -- 该方案可能会引起烧灼感。
 
burning, burning hot adj (extremely hot)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 炙热的 zhì rè de TC Traditional Chinese 炙熱的  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 滚烫的 zhì rè de，gǔn tàng de TC Traditional Chinese 滾燙的 
 -- Steph's skin was red from lying out in the burning sun.
 -- 躺在炙热的阳光下，让斯蒂芬的皮肤发红。
 
burning adj figurative (issue: urgent)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 迫切的 pò qiè de  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 紧要的 
 -- The burning problem is that so much is at stake.
 -- 最迫切的问题是，有太多事都岌岌可危了。
 
burning n (act of combusting)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 燃烧 rán shāo TC Traditional Chinese 燃燒  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 烧毁 rán shāo，shāo huǐ TC Traditional Chinese 燒毀 
 -- The burning of fossil fuels releases carbon dioxide.
 -- 化石燃料的燃烧会释放出二氧化碳。

其他翻译
 
burning n (destruction of for ideological reasons)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 焚烧抗议 TC Traditional Chinese 焚燒抗議  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 烧毁抗议 
 -- Many beautiful buildings were destroyed during the burning of Atlanta.

主要翻译
 
burn [sth] # vtr (set afire)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 烧毁, 烧掉, 烧坏  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 烧, 使燃烧, 使着火 
 -- He burned the documents so nobody would ever see them.
 -- 他把文件烧了，这样就再也没人能看到这些文件了。
 -- ⓘ 冬天他们烧柴取暖。
 
burn [sth] vtr (energy, calories)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 消耗 xiāo hào TC Traditional Chinese 消耗  (精力、能量等)
 -- Let the kids run around so they burn all their energy.
 -- 让孩子们到处跑跑，这样就会把精力都消耗掉了。
 
burn # vi (be on fire)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 燃烧 rán shāo TC Traditional Chinese 燃燒  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 烧着 rán shāo，shāo zhe 
 -- The log in the fireplace will burn for three hours.
 -- 壁炉里的木柴可以烧三个小时。
 
burn n (injury)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 烧伤，烫伤，灼伤 shāo shāng，tàng shāng，zhuó shāng  (高温、电击、腐蚀性化学物、辐射)
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 擦伤 cā shāng  (摩擦)
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 冻伤 dòng shāng  (寒冷)
 -- The burn took a week to heal.
 -- 那处烧伤花了一周才痊愈。
 -- ⓘ 他在攀岩时被绳子擦伤了。
 -- ⓘ 他在接触干冰时没戴手套，结果被冻伤了。
 
burn n (sunburn)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 晒伤，晒红 shài shāng，shài hóng  (太阳)
 -- He got a bad burn while lying in the sun at the pool yesterday.
 -- 昨天他躺在水池边太阳下，被晒伤得厉害。

