动词短语  burn  |  burning
 
burn away vi phrasal (be destroyed by fire)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 烧掉 shāo diào  
 
burn away vi phrasal (stay alight)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 持续燃烧  
 
burn [sth] away, burn away [sth] vtr phrasal sep (destroy by fire)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 烧毁, 烧光  
 
burn out vi phrasal (candle, bulb: be used up)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 燃尽而熄灭  (蜡烛等)
 -- The candle has completely burnt out.
 -- 那支蜡烛已经完全燃尽而熄灭。
 
burn out vi phrasal figurative (person: suffer overexhaustion)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 累垮 lèi kuǎ  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 耗尽体力 lèi kuǎ，hào jìn tǐ lì 
 -- Derek burnt out after working for so many months without a break.
 -- 数月无休的工作后，德雷克累垮了。
 
burn up vi phrasal US, slang, figurative (have a high fever)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 发高烧 TC Traditional Chinese 發高燒  
 -- When Cathy felt her son's forehead, he was burning up.
 -- 凯茜摸了儿子的额头，发现他在发烧。
 
burn [sb] up vtr phrasal sep US, slang, figurative (make very angry)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 使（某人）大怒 shǐ （ mǒu rén ） dà nù  
 -- It burns me up to see that man making my mum cry.
 -- 见到那个男人让我妈妈哭，这让我很生气。
 
burn up vi phrasal US, slang, figurative (be very angry)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 大怒 dà nù  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 暴怒 dà nù，bào nù 

复合形式：  burning  |  burn
 
book burning n (ideological: destroying books)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 焚书 fén shū  (通常由于意识形态的原因)
 -- The book burnings were motivated by the Church's objection to scientific thinking.
 -- 这次焚书是由于教会反对科学思维而引起的。
 
burning bush n (Bible: in Book of Exodus)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 燃烧的灌木，燃烧的荆棘 rán shāo de guàn mù，rán shāo de jīng jí  (《圣经》典故)
 
burning hot adj (intensely hot)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 灼热 zhuó rè TC Traditional Chinese 灼熱  
 -- The soup was burning hot.
 
burning issue n (urgent matter for discussion)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 急需讨论的紧要问题 jí xū tǎo lùn de jǐn yào wèn tí  
 -- Today's burning issue is deciding where to go for lunch.
 
burning issue n (keenly-debated topic)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 热烈争论的问题 rè liè zhēng lùn de wèn tí  
 -- Religion is always a burning issue.
 
burning pain n (pain with a hot sensation)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 灼痛  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 烧灼痛 
 
burning question n (urgent matter for discussion)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 急需讨论的紧要问题 jí xū tǎo lùn de jǐn yào wèn tí  
 
burning question n (question needing an urgent answer)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 急待回答的问题 jí dài huí dá de wèn tí  
 -- I have a burning question. I need to know when you saw him last.
 
burning up adj figurative, informal (with fever)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 发烧的 fā shāo de  
 -- I felt Samantha's forehead: she was burning up.
 
dittany, gas plant, burning bush, fraxinella n (aromatic herb)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 白鲜  (芳香草本植物)
 
oil-burning adj (using oil as fuel)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 烧油的，燃油的  
 -- There is an oil-burning stove in the kitchen.
 
slow-burning adj (fuel: taking a long time to burn)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 耐烧的，慢燃的  (燃料)
 
slow-burning adj figurative (emotion: taking time to build)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 缓慢滋生的，日积月累的  (情绪)
 
slow-burning adj figurative (story: taking time to develop)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 进展缓慢的  (故事)
 
wood burner, wood-burning stove, log burner n (heating appliance fueled by wood)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 烧木柴的炉子  (取暖炉)
 
wood-burning stove n (cooker: fueled by wood)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 烧木头的炉子  

